327911,86,585,13,37,1,159,20,"‘ yassa kho pana te atthāya dhammo desito, so na niyyāti takkarassa sammā dukkhakkhayāyā’ ti, tamahaṃ tattha sādhukaṃ samanuyuñjeyyaṃ samanugāheyyaṃ samanubhāseyyaṃ. "
327912,86,585,38,84,1,368,38,"So vata mayā sādhukaṃ samanuyuñjiyamāno samanugāhiyamāno samanubhāsiyamāno aṭṭhānametaṃ anavakāso yaṃ so tiṇṇaṃ ṭhānānaṃ nāññataraṃ ṭhānaṃ nigaccheyya, aññena vā aññaṃ paṭicarissati, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmessati, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukarissati, tuṇhībhūto maṅkubhūto pattakkhandho adhomukho pajjhāyanto appaṭibhāno nisīdissati, seyyathāpi sarabho paribbājako’’ ti. "
327913,86,585,85,95,1,91,10,Atha kho bhagavā sippinikātīre paribbājakārāme tikkhattuṃ sīhanādaṃ naditvā vehāsaṃ pakkāmi. 
327914,86,586,2,45,1,121,11,"Atha kho te paribbājakā acirapakkantassa bhagavato sarabhaṃ paribbājakaṃ samantato vācāyasannitodakena[ vācāsattitodakena( sī.)] sañjambharimakaṃsu[ sañcumbharimakaṃsu( pī., dī. ni.1.421) saṃ. ni.2.243 uparipāṭho viya]–"
327915,86,586,46,85,1,115,12,"‘‘ seyyathāpi, āvuso sarabha, brahāraññe jarasiṅgālo‘ sīhanādaṃ nadissāmī’ ti siṅgālakaṃyeva[ segālakaṃyeva( sī. syā. kaṃ. pī.)] nadati, bheraṇḍakaṃyeva nadati[ bhedaṇḍakaṃ( ka.)]; "
327916,86,586,86,106,1,127,15,"evamevaṃ kho tvaṃ, āvuso sarabha, aññatreva samaṇena gotamena‘ sīhanādaṃ nadissāmī’ ti siṅgālakaṃyeva nadasi bheraṇḍakaṃyeva nadasi. "
327917,86,586,107,144,1,99,9,"Seyyathāpi, āvuso sarabha, ambukasañcarī[ ambakamaddarī( sī.)]‘ purisakaravitaṃ[ phussakaravitaṃ( sī.), pussakaravitaṃ( syā. kaṃ. pī.)] ravissāmī’ ti ambukasañcariravitaṃyeva ravati; "
327918,86,586,145,163,1,120,13,"evamevaṃ kho tvaṃ, āvuso sarabha, aññatreva samaṇena gotamena‘ purisakaravitaṃ ravissāmī’ ti, ambukasañcariravitaṃyeva ravasi. "
327919,86,586,164,175,1,77,9,"Seyyathāpi, āvuso sarabha, usabho suññāya gosālāya gambhīraṃ naditabbaṃ maññati; "
327920,86,586,176,192,1,91,12,"evamevaṃ kho tvaṃ, āvuso sarabha, aññatreva samaṇena gotamena gambhīraṃ naditabbaṃ maññasī’’ ti. "
327921,86,586,193,203,1,96,9,Atha kho te paribbājakā sarabhaṃ paribbājakaṃ samantato vācāyasannitodakena sañjambharimakaṃsūti. 
